folder: 123rd Street (East) - Second Avenue - Third Avenue, Manhattan, NY
title: 123rd Street (East) - Second Avenue - Third Avenue

text:
218-244 East 123rd Street, west of, adjoining, and at the S.W. corner of Second Avenue. In the foreground is a row of four three-story frame houses.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.

Second Ave., east side, north from and including East 123rd Street, showing the Palace Theatre (motion pictures) bearing Nos. 2404-2408 and a portion of the Second Ave. Elevated Line. Also seen (right) is No. 301-305 East 123rd Street, a 1-story brick house (covered with posters) at the N.E. corner of Second Ave.

May 7, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
